From GPT: Here&#8217;s the expert-level diagnosis for the EcoFlow Ocean Pro / Smart Home Panel based on the error in your screenshot.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#9989; ERROR: &#8220;SHP Issues Command to Shut Down PCS (1809)&#8221;
&#160;
Cause of Fault (from app):
&#160;
&#8220;MBS/SHP40 released, PCS stopped working.&#8221;
&#160;
What this means in simple terms:
&#160;
The Smart Home Panel (SHP) is telling the PCS (Power Conversion System) inside the Ocean Pro inverter to shut down because one of the following has happened:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A breaker or internal relay in the SHP opened unexpectedly
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The MBS (Main Breaker Switch) or SHP40 module dropped out
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A communication or power interruption occurred between the SHP and the inverter
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The SHP senses unsafe grid or wiring conditions and forces a shutdown
&#160;
PCS shutdown &#8800; inverter failure.
It means the SHP forced the inverter offline for protection.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#9989; MOST COMMON REAL-WORLD CAUSES (TriSMART field experience)
&#160;
1&#65039;&#8419; Loose or unseated SHP40 module
&#160;
This is the #1 cause.
If the SHP40 is not fully locked into the bus, the SHP sends a shutdown command.
&#160;
2&#65039;&#8419; Loose terminals in SHP (L1, L2, N, or CT connections)
&#160;
EcoFlow equipment is extremely sensitive to loose lugs.
&#160;
3&#65039;&#8419; Grid frequency/voltage out of range
&#160;
If the SHP detects abnormal grid conditions for even 1 second, PCS is forced offline.
&#160;
4&#65039;&#8419; Breaker feeding the Ocean Pro inverter opened or tripped
&#160;
This includes:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Backfeed breaker at main panel
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;SHP internal relay
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Inverter AC input breaker
&#160;
5&#65039;&#8419; Firmware mismatch between Smart Home Panel and Ocean Pro
&#160;
If the SHP and inverter are not on compatible firmware, they fight each other and throw error 1809.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#9989; STEP-BY-STEP FIX (Do these in this exact order)
&#160;
1. Power cycle the entire EcoFlow system (clean reset)
&#160;
Do this in order:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;1.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Turn OFF:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ocean Pro AC breaker
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ocean Pro DC switch (battery)
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;SHP main breaker (MBS)
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Wait 60 seconds
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Turn ON in this order:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;SHP (MBS)
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ocean Pro DC (battery)
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ocean Pro AC breaker
&#160;
&#9888;&#65039; This clears 80% of 1809 errors.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
2. Check SHP40 module physically
&#160;
Open SHP cover (if you&#8217;re the installer/tech):
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Push the SHP40 module firmly into the bus
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ensure both side locking tabs snap in
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Tug-test it&#8212;should not move at all
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Visually confirm copper bus is fully inserted
&#160;
Loose SHP40 = instant 1809 shutdown.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
3. Check wiring torque on all SHP lugs
&#160;
Use correct torque:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;L1, L2, Neutral feeding inverter
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Load circuits supplying smart loads
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Grid input lugs
&#160;
Loose lugs = SHP thinks breaker dropped.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
4. Confirm breakers
&#160;
Check:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The breaker feeding inverter is ON
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Inverter AC breaker inside SHP didn&#8217;t trip
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Smart Home Panel internal relay is ON (your APP shows it, check each load)
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
5. Update ALL firmware
&#160;
Open EcoFlow app:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;SHP firmware
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Ocean Pro firmware
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Power Hub firmware (if used)
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Battery firmware
&#160;
Tap device > Updates > Install ALL.
&#160;
Firmware mismatch is a known cause of 1809.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
6. Grid instability check
&#160;
Using a meter:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Verify grid voltage 240V &#177; 10%
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Frequency 60Hz &#177; 0.2
&#160;
EcoFlow shuts down FAST if unstable.
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
7. Battery communications check
&#160;
If a battery is offline or low voltage during discharge, PCS shuts down.
&#160;
Look for:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Battery not recognized
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Battery at <5%
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Battery BMS warning
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#129520; If the error returns immediately (important):
&#160;
It means the SHP thinks its internal relay or SHP40 module is OPEN even when physically closed.
&#160;
This is usually:
&#160;
&#128295; A bad SHP40 module
&#160;
or
&#160;
&#128295; A firmware bug requiring regeneration of the relay status
&#160;
Try removing SHP40 from the bus and reinstalling it.
&#160;
If still fails &#8594; Replace SHP40 or entire SHP (EcoFlow RMA).
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#128204; Most Likely Fix for THIS specific job (TriSMART context)
&#160;
Based on the screenshot:
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Solar is producing
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Home is pulling 837W
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Batteries are discharging 122W
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Grid says 0W (this is suspicious)
&#160;
This tells me:
&#160;
The SHP grid relay is NOT closed.
&#160;
The SHP thinks grid is disconnected &#8594; It shuts down PCS &#8594; Error 1809.
&#160;
That points to:
&#160;
&#10004; Loose SHP40
&#160;
&#10004; Internal relay not engaging
&#160;
&#10004; Breaker feeding inverter is open
&#160;
&#10004; Firmware mismatch
&#160;
&#11835;
&#160;
&#9989; Final Diagnosis
&#160;
The Smart Home Panel has released the SHP40 or detected an open relay, which caused the Ocean Pro inverter&#8217;s PCS to shut down for safety. The SHP is essentially dropping grid connection even though the system appears powered. Fix is to reseat the SHP40,
torque all lugs, power-cycle the system, and ensure firmware matches

Give it about 5-8 minutes to let it start up. As long as we start up okay, then we are in the clear.&#160;
